    <p>
      Algebra is a branch of mathematics that focuses on structures that arise from equipping a space with one or more finitary operations.
      Roughly speaking, algebraic structures are generally <term>discrete</term> (the opposite of continuous) in the sense that they do not involve (analytic) limits.
    </p>
